  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] They were friends of my father-- one, who was a teacher of mathematics, who was actually a professor of mathematics.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Of course, these student-- these professors did not get much money.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they always were tutoring",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father saw to it that I learned English, mathematics.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I continued very, very good education.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, in fact, I acquired certain studying habits, which were, in fact, superior and served me very well in the future.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because most of the time children spend in classes are wasted and utterly boring because you sit in a group of 20, 30 people listening to stuff which is immaterial and most likely something that you really are not interested in doing anyway.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whereas, I remember 1940 and '41 as an opportunity to acquire the habit of independent learning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I started wearing the yellow star early in 1942.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, this was-- as a precursor for the deportations to make sure that you nab everybody, you first enforce the yellow star rule.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, my, my-- you know, the question was, what coat?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, there was a limited supply of yellow stars.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the question is which jacket do you put it on?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, oh yes, it, it was a, a sense of embarrassment.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But by that time, of course, you knew you were stripped.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, you have gone through two years of stripping-- you know, no radio, no books, no movies, no music, prescribed places where you can live, curfews.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No fur coats was a big deal, no fur coats-- a law that Jews cannot have a fur coat.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first deportations began in 1942.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
